# Development Standards

## Philosophy

**Declarative first.** Flow > Validation Rule > Formula > Apex. Apex is a last resort. When Apex is required, follow Part 2 of this document.

This document defines the target state. Existing metadata is not required to be retroactively renamed or refactored, but all new and modified components must follow these standards.

### Verification Stage

Each section is tagged with when it can be verified:

- **Design** — checkable in the design document before build begins. `/design-review` and `/backlog graduate` enforce these.
- **Build** — checkable only when actual code or metadata exists. Enforced during build sessions and `/validate-build`.

New sections added to this document must include a `**Verify:** Design | Build` line.

